This exact time last year, I was in a terribly dark place. I felt so empty, and the only thing I could grasp to explain myself was - I’m so tired of being tired.  It was a phrase that haunted me everyday.  Everything changed for me at the end of last year. I decided to take control of my life and my happiness.  I stopped drinking, I decided to start auditioning again, fell in love with exercise again and reclaimed my voice.  I consider myself so so lucky that with the cancer I had last year, it did not impact my day to day life but it took a huge emotional toll on me. It woke me up.  Quite literally made me realize I had been going through the motions of life and I was desperately unhappy. I hadn’t been on a stage in five years.  How was that possible?? And I was about to under go a very invasive surgery on a part of my body I needed the most to perform - my throat.  I told my surgeon before we went into the operating room, “Please be careful. I am a performer, I could probably become a mime if something happens but I need my voice.” 😂💀 And here I am 8 months later, singing on stage with such a kind and incredibly talented cast (and the freakin best crew). Sometimes, I feel like the luckiest girl on the planet. 

We had a successful opening weekend!!! Only two more weekends to see this spectacular show with an all-star cast. I’m so proud of everyone involved.  Ticket link in bio and DM me with any questions! ✨

🔥107 Orange Theory classes
💫307 days of sobriety 
🍪7 million cookies consumed 😂

⭐️milestones can happen at any point in your life journey! we don’t talk a lot about the grieving process that happens when you shed a past version of yourself…I’m still undeniably weird so don’t worry about that. 😂 

A few things I love about @orangetheory because the list is long: 
1. It’s you against you, though the people around you give you energy! 
2. The coaches. The work they put into each class is insane. 
3. The front desk staff - multi tasking heroes! 
4. The music.  Not everyone wants to go to the club during a workout but hey, I like to relive my rave days somehow. 
5. It’s the only workout I’ve been able to stay consistent with and it has rewarded me with real results I can see and feel. Patience and consistency is everything. 

I talk about @orangetheory so much, I’m sure everyone is tired of me, but members have been given referral codes! So if you have been inspired to sign up please use the below. 🥹

🚨Referral Code: 
WZZQ85

And if you ever have questions about resources that I’ve used for my sobriety journey my DM’s are open. 🧡

2023 was the year I decided to fully embrace who I am to it’s core.  I got back into theatre, met the love of my life, traveled to DC, NYC, LA, Gatlinburg, Williamsburg, Florida and Tokyo (I am finally unpacked) and celebrated a year of sobriety.  Oh, and seeing Shania Twain, Taylor Swift and Dolly Parton just about made my heart explode.  On New Years Day I am preparing to head back into rehearsals for Silent Sky (details for performances soon!) It’s a magnificent play that so eloquently encapsulates the questions to answers we all long for…and may never know. But we do not need to know everything, do we? ✨✨
